snippet: Al Qaeda’s Iraqi wing says it masterminded a jailbreak in the northern city of Tikrit last month and smuggled weapons to inmates, according to a statement posted Friday on militant Web sites.
abstract: Al Qaeda’s Iraqi wing says it masterminded jailbreak in city of Tikrit and smuggled weapons to inmates; dozens of prisoners, many of them convicted members of Al Qaeda on death row, fought their way out of jail, killing 16 members of  the security forces.
lead_paragraph: Al Qaeda’s Iraqi wing says it masterminded a jailbreak in the northern city of Tikrit last month and smuggled weapons to inmates, according to a statement posted Friday on militant Web sites.
